title: For Sale:  Maryland Wear and Carry Permit Training Class June 2018
postcontent: On saturday and sunday June 23 and 24 2018 a training class for the Maryland State Concealed (Wear and Carry) Firearm Permit will be conducted in Bowie, Maryland from 8:00am-4:00pm both days. This training class is open to anyone not legally disqualified from owning or having access to firearms or ammunition. Concealed Firearm Permits are available in Maryland to private citizens, business owners, security personnell, and correctional institution personnell. Topics presented and discussed in this class include Maryland Law, Duty to Retreat, Use of Deadly Force, Legal and Moral Implications, Firearm  Safety, Firearm Nomenclature, Cartridge Structure and Selection, Sight Alignment/Sight Picture, Position Shooting, Use of Cover and Concealment, Clothing Selection, Dry-Fire Exercises, Live-Fire Range Exercises, and Final Qualifications. Attendees are required to provide their chosen firearm for concealed carry, a strong side holster specific to their chosen firearm, 200 rounds of factory loaded ammunition, and eye and hearing protection. ALL AMERICAN Small Arms Training will provide printed material handouts, pens, note paper, chamber flags, and targets for the classroom and live-fire respectively. Taking and passing this training class does not guarantee you will be issued a a concealed firearm permit in Maryland, or any other state or jurisdiction. Concealed firearm permits are issued at the discretion of the Maryland State Police Licensing Division. Initial permit training and renewal permit training will be conducted in the same class, please contact instructor for details and registration information. Pre-registration is required for this training class and should be completed not later than thursday 21 June 2018. The cost of this training class is $175.00 for permit renewal training (8 hours) , and $350.00 for initial permit training (16 hours). To register for this class, or to have any questions answered, please call instructor at 202 664-6729 or respond to this post via e-mail.
